PS: *personally, I&#39;d suggest (and I am in accordance with Kent Beck on this, see his [implementation patterns](http://www.informit.com/store/product.aspx?isbn=0321413091) book) to put the nested loops in a separate method and then break out with `return` but that will cast the anger of the &quot;single return point&quot; folks upon me. Internet, oh, internet.*

